    "notes": "Vendor: Roche / KAPA Biosystems, KAPA Taq DNA Polymerase / KAPA Taq PCR Kit (TDS KR0352). Annealing: Tm minus 5 C as a starting point (the 55 C shown is a placeholder; optimize by gradient). 1X buffer = 1.5 mM MgCl2. Use up to 2.5 U per 25 uL for GC-rich/difficult templates; add 5% DMSO for GC-rich. Use 5 min at 95 C for the initial denaturation with >65% GC templates. The optional final extension (72 C, 1 min/kb) helps when TA-cloning. 35 cycles. Amplifies up to ~3.5 kb genomic / 5 kb less-complex. Cycling and 1X concentrations were cross-confirmed firsthand against the KAPA Taq ReadyMix TDS (KR0354). Source: Roche/KAPA KAPA Taq PCR Kit Technical Data Sheet (KR0352)."
